The Common Development and Distribution License (CDDL-1.0) license is a
recognized open source license by the Open Source Initiative:
http://opensource.org/licenses/CDDL-1.0

The zlib/libpng license is a recognized "\"free\"" software license by the
Free Software Foundation: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/license-list.html#CDDL
However, the FSF doesn't like it and won't allow a CDDL-licensed "module" to
be linked with a GNU GPL "module".
